ssor Bordas had explained that the\nParis rat could boast of a family tree\ndating back to the early centuries of the\nChristian era. having emigrated to\nNear East with the\n1' ranee from the\nearly Crusader\u00ab.\nSuch aristociats\nare bound to put\nup a stiff fight for their privileges.\"\nsaid a honorons member of the com\nmission.\nw\ni priced medicine loosens and clears mu\nj cus and phlegm, checks strangling\nRecommended to School Children.\nThis is the season when children aro\nsubject to croup, colds and coughs. Rena\nC. Marchard, 36 Lawrence St., Salem.\nMass-, writes: \"I used Foley's Honey\nand Tar with good results. 1 had a very\nbad cold and it gave me relief at once,\nso I recommend it to every child that\ngoes to school.\" This standard, low\nj coughing, makes easy breathing, soothes\nj and heals raw, inflamed membranes, and\nstops tickling in throat.. Great Fall\u00ab\nj Drug Co.\u2014Adv.\nThe body of Alric. celebrated king of\nthe Visigoths, was burried in the bed of\na river to hide ir from the Romans whom\nj he had conquered.\nI Marine shells of warm climates ex\nceed all others in beauty of coloring and\nin taking a high polish..","height":"22704","width":"17568"}}
